  "text": "Chromium's multi-process architecture is defined by five key components:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h): The browser-side representation of a renderer process. This class (defined at line 195) implements the RenderProcessHost interface and serves as the main communication point between the browser process and each renderer process. It inherits from multiple interfaces including ChildProcessLauncher::Client and mojom::RendererHost.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h): The main browser process event loop (defined at line 106). This class orchestrates the initialization and shutdown of the browser's main thread, managing thread creation, message loops, and various browser components.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h): The main thread of a renderer process (defined at line 126). This class represents the renderer process's main thread where blink::WebView instances live, and it handles most communication through mojo IPC messages with some legacy IPC messages. It implements the mojom::Renderer interface.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h): Responsible for spawning child processes (defined at line 212). This class handles the asynchronous launching of child processes and notifies clients when the process is ready or fails to launch.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** (content/common/renderer.mojom): The Mojo interface (defined at line 49) that declares the browser-to-renderer communication contract. This is a Channel-associated interface that implements browser-to-renderer control messages, including methods like CreateAgentSchedulingGroup and CreateAssociatedAgentSchedulingGroup.\n\nThese components form the core of Chromium's multi-process architecture, establishing a clear separation between the browser process and renderer processes with well-defined IPC/Mojo communication interfaces."
}

